# Agent Rules & Preferences

## Terminal & Commands
- **Environment:** Windows PowerShell
- **Command Chaining:** ALWAYS use `;` instead of `&&` to chain terminal commands. The `&&` operator causes parser errors in this specific PowerShell version.
- **Example:** `git commit -am "msg"; git push` (DO NOT USE `&&`)

## Coding & Framework
- **Stack:** Next.js, React, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui.
- **Paths:** Always use absolute paths for tools unless relative paths are explicitly required.

## Workflow Rules
- **Git Auto-Push:** Every time you complete a user request, you MUST automatically commit and push the changes to git. Use the command `git add .; git commit -m "Auto-commit: <brief description of changes>"; git push`
